snippet.textDisplay: People can talk about how crappy a lot of games are on release, and even wonder if greed fuels everything about these games. But, I like to look at it as, you can always start being better. Turn things around. No matter how bad and bankrupt a game may start, you can fix things and make it great. Instead of giving up on a game almost immediately and screwing over the people that bought it in the beginning.
